column48: In person programming labs/workshop. I remember in first year joao was quite short with people when they had questions that were obviously because they weren’t paying attention. That’s going to happen if it’s all remote because it’s not very stimulating, I think in person would switch people on more and they will ask more insightful questions and then hopefully demonstrators will have more patience. My first coding experiences was so scary and intimidating it put me off for my whole degree and I’m only just understanding it’s soemthing I can’t avoid. I feel like if I had a better introduction I’d be less intimidated - there should be emphasis or maybe a seperate class for people who have never coded before who need more patience and empathy. Being treated like a computer didn’t make me feel good at all
